  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering can result in significant criminal penalties, including:\n\n1. Potential prison sentences:\n- Up to 20 years in federal prison per offense\n- Maximum sentences can vary based on specific circumstances\n\n2. Financial penalties:\n- Substantial fines, often up to $500,000 or twice the value of the property involved\n- Potential forfeiture of assets connected to the laundering activity\n\n3. Additional consequences:\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential deportation for non-citizens\n\nThe exact penalties depend on factors like the amount of money involved, specific federal statutes violated, and individual case details. Prosecution typically occurs under statutes like the Bank Secrecy Act and Money Laundering Control Act.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering penalties?",
